00:02:48.440 --> 00:02:56.119
company that Prudential is, there's in that regulated industry, there's a lot of focus on

00:02:56.759 --> 00:03:03.639
us demonstrating that we manage risk. And there's two kinds of risk. There's financial risk,

00:03:03.639 --> 00:03:10.039
which is kind of like the ability for the company to manage fluctuations in the market

00:03:11.080 --> 00:03:20.279
and fluctuations in regarding to the actuarial models that we have. So COVID was a fun one for

00:03:20.279 --> 00:03:25.960
that. But then there's also operational risk and COVID was a fun one for that as well.

00:03:26.839 --> 00:03:35.479
As an organization, we have to be able to manage disruptions as far as weather-related events,

00:03:36.199 --> 00:03:45.960
sales practices, fraud, cyber attacks, all of that. And the Operational Risk Management

00:03:45.960 --> 00:03:54.520
Department is responsible for that. And at a very high level, we are responsible for calculating

00:03:54.520 --> 00:04:01.720
what's called risk-adjusted capital, which is a number that is tied to how much operational risk

00:04:01.720 --> 00:04:10.279
we have. And so the less risk we can demonstrate, the less of that capital we as a company need to

00:04:10.279 --> 00:04:16.679
hold aside. And of course, cash flow is king. The more money you can freely move around,

00:04:16.679 --> 00:04:21.720
the more flexible you are as a company. So that's the importance of our role within Prudential.

