00:06:00.279 --> 00:06:06.119
you need to be fully aware of your business processes, and you need to be aware of the

00:06:06.200 --> 00:06:10.920
fully aware of your business processes. You need to know who is responsible for them,

00:06:10.920 --> 00:06:18.119
who are the key subject matter experts in that process. And you kind of want to spread them out

00:06:18.119 --> 00:06:26.440
so that if there are scenarios that impact a very geographically centered location,

00:06:26.440 --> 00:06:33.720
that you don't have everybody living there so that you can adjust for those scenarios. So that's

00:06:34.679 --> 00:06:41.559
what we kind of try to express in a number associated to each business process,

00:06:42.119 --> 00:06:47.239
so that the stakeholders that own that business process can think to themselves, okay, maybe we,

00:06:47.799 --> 00:06:52.679
it's time for like a rotation of some resources that are associated to them.

00:06:55.079 --> 00:07:01.880
