00:07:01.880 --> 00:07:07.880
team's working on or maybe a past project? I think that helps us understand your challenges

00:07:07.880 --> 00:07:20.279
and team goals too. Yeah. So a big one that I can describe is we try to express our

00:07:21.079 --> 00:07:31.640
IT incidents in their impact to business processes. And the thing is that when something

00:07:31.640 --> 00:07:39.799
in a data center goes down, a ticket gets raised and they say computer ABC is, you know,

00:07:39.799 --> 00:07:46.440
hard drive is full or memory issues or CPU needs to be upgraded or something like that.

00:07:46.920 --> 00:07:53.640
But that doesn't make it possible for a business owner to understand what that really means.

00:07:54.200 --> 00:08:05.880
And so within our IT system, there's this giant list of, you know, all these assets and

00:08:05.880 --> 00:08:12.920
it's a giant graph, a network of all these pieces that are combined. And so our team created a

00:08:13.000 --> 00:08:20.920
network out of that and calculated which business processes are impacted if

00:08:21.559 --> 00:08:25.000
something goes down or needs to be replaced or, yeah.

