00:16:23.640 --> 00:16:29.479
that, for instance, determine a quote for a life insurance policy or things like that,

00:16:31.000 --> 00:16:39.239
obviously, if there's an issue with that, they create financial risk. But the development of it

00:16:39.239 --> 00:16:45.320
and the processes around it and the rigor that's put in the whole development of that

00:16:45.320 --> 00:16:53.479
is an operational risk, because that's like a process risk. And so that really,

00:16:54.520 --> 00:17:02.039
that whole process of model risk governance is what controls the quality of the model. So the

00:17:03.000 --> 00:17:11.160
